with this:

```css
.right-illustration {
    width: 600px;
    height: 804px;
    border-top-left-radius: 40px;
    overflow: hidden;
    background: #154734;
}

.right-illustration img {
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
    object-fit: contain;
    object-position: center center;
}
```

If the image still looks duplicated, then you exported the wrong layer from Figma.

Export only the full parent:

```text
Illustration_right
```

not:

```text
Mascot
Finger Like
Pattern round
Background
```

